28/12/2006
PRIZREN, Kosovo, Serbia -- Bulgarian Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov said he is optimistic regarding the resolution of the Kosovo status problem, during a visit to the province on Wednesday (December 27th).
He and Bulgarian army chief General Zlatan Stoykov were in Prizren to meet with Bulgarian troops serving in KFOR and with senior KFOR representatives.
Bliznakov did not comment on what the future status might be, saying only that the solution should respect existing borders, strengthen regional security and help develop the region's economy and infrastructure.
(BNR, BTA - 27/12/06)
